# which endpoints are public
All endpoints are public.
Allowed HTTP methods are restricted per endpoint.

# which field are required on create
POST -> strict
PATCH -> flexible 
PUT -> not supported in v1.

# Request / Response format

Clients send JSON requests
Server returns JSON responses

# what clients are allowed to edit.

Edit permissions are defined per resource and per endpoint.


# what errors are guaranteed?

clients can rely on:

-HTTP status code
-consistent error shapes
-validation messages

# what is forbidden?

Submitting more than one response for the same question is forbidden.


# who is allowed to use?

Public(no auth)
But still restricted by behaviour



TextQuestionContainer

### POST /api/container

purpose: Create a text question container

# Mandatory values
-title

# Optional Values
-description 
-is_active

# Editable fields via PATCH
-title
-description 


### PATCH /api/container/{id}

purpose: Edit a text question container

# Editable fields

-title 
-description

-----------------------------------------

TextQuestion 
------------

### POST /api/question

purpose: Create a text question

# Mandatory values

-title 

-text_question_container

-question_number_id

# Optional values

-is_active

# Editable fields via PATCH

-title
-is_active

# Immutable fields

-question_number_id
-text_question_container


### PATCH /api/question/{id}/

purpose:  Edit a text question

# Editable

-title
-is_active

------------------------------------------

TextResponse 
------------

### POST /api/question/{question_id}/responses/

purpose: Submit a response

# Mandatory Values
- response_text


# Optional values

- response_number_id

# Immutable values

- response_number_id


###   PATCH /api/response/{id}/

purpose: Edit a response 


# Editable values

- response_text


# Non editable values

- text_question
- response_number_id
